---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n';
const tr = useTranslations('en');
---
<Base title="LACET · Contest rules" lang="en">

  <header class="corner">
    <div class="corner-left">
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span>{tr.region}</span>
    </div>
    <div class="corner-right">
      <a href="/en/sondage" class="back">← Survey</a>
      <nav class="lang-switcher">
        <a href="/concours-reglement">FR</a>
        <span class="lang-sep">·</span>
        <span class="lang-active">EN</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="content-page">
      <h1>Contest rules</h1>
      <div class="subtitle">Last updated: April 2026</div>

      <p>
        These rules govern entry into the prize draw organized by Lacet as part of the service
        validation survey. By entering, you accept the conditions below.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Organizer</h2>
      <p>
        The contest is organized by Lacet (Québec, Canada). For any question, write to
        <a href="mailto:info@lacet.ca">info@lacet.ca</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Contest period</h2>
      <p>
        The contest begins on <strong>Saturday, May 16, 2026 at 12:00&nbsp;a.m.</strong> and
        ends on <strong>Saturday, June 6, 2026 at 11:59&nbsp;p.m.</strong> (Eastern Time).
        Any entry received outside this period will be automatically disqualified.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
      <p>
        The contest is open to anyone aged 18 or over who legally resides in Canada at the
        time of entry, except:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Lacet's employees, officers, directors and representatives;</li>
        <li>members of the immediate family (parent, sibling, spouse, child) of the persons
          listed above, as well as anyone living at the same address as those persons.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. How to enter</h2>
      <p>To be entered into the draw, the participant must:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Complete the Lacet survey available at
          <a href="https://www.lacet.ca/en/sondage">https://www.lacet.ca/en/sondage</a>
          by answering all required questions;</li>
        <li>Check the <strong>"I'd like to enter the draw"</strong> box at the bottom of the
          survey and provide their full name and a valid email address;</li>
        <li>Accept these rules.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Entry is <strong>free and no purchase is necessary</strong>. Only one entry per person
        is allowed, regardless of the number of email addresses used. Any attempt at multiple
        entries will result in disqualification.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Prize</h2>
      <p>
        One (1) prize will be awarded: a <strong>Garmin Varia RearVue 820</strong>
        (rear radar with integrated camera for cyclists), with an approximate retail value of
        <strong>$419.99 CAD before taxes</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The prize is non-cashable, non-transferable, non-exchangeable and must be accepted as
        awarded. Applicable taxes, if any, are the responsibility of the winner. Lacet will
        cover delivery of the prize to an address in Canada designated by the winner.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Draw and skill-testing question</h2>
      <p>
        The draw will take place on <strong>Monday, June 8, 2026</strong> at Lacet's head office,
        by computerized random draw, from all valid entries received during the contest period.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before being declared the winner, the selected person must
        <strong>correctly answer, without help, a mathematical skill-testing question</strong>
        sent to them by email. As an example, the question will take the following form:
        <em>(15&nbsp;×&nbsp;4) + 27&nbsp;−&nbsp;8 = ?</em>
      </p>

      <h2>7. Claiming the prize</h2>
      <p>
        The selected person will be contacted by email at the address provided at entry, within
        seven (7) days following the draw. They will have <strong>fourteen (14) days</strong>
        from the date that email is sent to:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Correctly answer the mathematical skill-testing question;</li>
        <li>Sign a declaration and release form releasing Lacet from any liability related to
          the prize or its claim;</li>
        <li>Confirm their eligibility (age, residency, no employment or family ties with Lacet);</li>
        <li>Provide a delivery address in Canada.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Failing a complete response within the prescribed period, the selected person will be
        deemed to have forfeited the prize and a new draw may be held among the remaining
        entries.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Use of personal information</h2>
      <p>
        The name and email address provided as part of the contest are used
        <strong>solely</strong> to manage the draw, contact the winner and arrange delivery of
        the prize. This information is kept separately from your survey answers, which remain
        anonymous. It will be deleted no later than <strong>sixty (60) days</strong> after the
        prize is awarded.
      </p>
      <p>
        Subscribing to the Lacet newsletter is entirely separate and optional; it is not a
        condition of entry into the contest.
      </p>
      <p>
        For more details on how your data is handled, see our
        <a href="/en/privacy">privacy policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        Lacet, its employees, partners, suppliers and representatives accept no liability in
        any case where their inability to act results from a fact or situation beyond their
        control, including a strike, lock-out, labour dispute, technical, computer or
        telecommunications failure, or any case of force majeure.
      </p>
      <p>
        Lacet is not responsible for entries that are lost, misdirected, incomplete, illegible,
        delayed or not received for any reason. Any entry will be deemed submitted by the
        person who is the holder of the email address provided.
      </p>
      <p>
        Lacet declines all liability for the use of the prize by the winner, its loss, or any
        damage that may result from it.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Final decisions</h2>
      <p>
        Any decision by Lacet or its representatives regarding the organization, conduct and
        awarding of the prize in this contest is final and without appeal, subject to any
        contrary decision by the Régie des alcools, des courses et des jeux du Québec.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes and cancellation</h2>
      <p>
        Lacet reserves the right, at its sole discretion, to amend these rules, suspend or
        cancel the contest in exceptional circumstances, subject to the prior approval of the
        Régie des alcools, des courses et des jeux du Québec where required. Any notice will be
        published on lacet.ca.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Disputes — Régie des alcools, des courses et des jeux du Québec</h2>
      <p>
        A dispute regarding the organization or conduct of an advertising contest may be
        submitted to the Régie des alcools, des courses et des jeux du Québec for resolution.
        A dispute regarding the awarding of a prize may be submitted to the Régie only for an
        intervention to attempt to resolve it.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Acceptance of the rules</h2>
      <p>
        By entering the contest, the participant accepts the terms of these rules and
        acknowledges that Lacet's decisions are final and without appeal, subject to
        section&nbsp;12.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Any question regarding the contest can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:info@lacet.ca">info@lacet.ca</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer lang="en" />

</Base>
